OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1779117068
OL,3,CStarmer's Government returns to
OL,4,CWestminster amid leadership rivals'
OL,5,CBrexit row
OL,7,FSir Keir Starmer, who reportedly spent
OL,8,Fthe weekend at his Chequers country
OL,9,Festate, is said to be privately
OL,10,Fconsidering whether he will contest
OL,11,Fchallenges to his leadership, despite
OL,12,Fhaving publicly insisted he will fight
OL,13,Fthem.
OL,15,FMs Nandy appeared to veer away from
OL,16,Fthe Government line that Sir Keir
OL,17,Fwould stand against his rivals as she
OL,18,Fspoke to broadcasters on Sunday
OL,19,Fmorning, telling the BBC: "It's a very
OL,20,Fpersonal decision for him."
OL,26,@{D@[OU|D@[O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
